# Servers — JSON array; never expose to frontend. Add multiple servers as needed.
# Auth (pick one, api_token preferred for new 3X-UI panels):
#   api_token   — Bearer token from panel Settings → Security → API Token.
#   username + password — legacy cookie-session login (fallback).
# Optional: scheme (http|https, default http), base_path (e.g. "/xui"),
#           sub_uri, sub_path, sub_port (override subscription link host/port/path;
#           default https://<domain>:2096/sub/<subId>).
# Fields: name, ip|url, port, scheme, base_path, api_token|username+password,
#         inbound_id, status (enabled|disabled), sub_uri, sub_port
SERVERS=[{"name":"server1","url":"https://example:2087/abcd/","api_token":"your-panel-api-token","username":"abcd","password":"abcd","status":"enabled","sub_uri":"https://example:1234/sssuuubbb"}]
